+A file descriptor in the URL takes precedence over the @option{fd} option and
+must be a nonnegative decimal integer. If neither form specifies a descriptor,
+the stdout file descriptor is used for writing and stdin for reading. Unlike
+the pipe protocol, the fd protocol has seek support when the descriptor
+corresponds to a regular file. On the Darwin build, seekable fd contexts use
+positional I/O and maintain independent logical positions, so reopening the
+same inherited descriptor does not share an offset. The descriptor must allow
+every requested operation; MP4 faststart output requires read and write access.
+Streamed descriptors retain sequential read and write behavior.
 
 This protocol accepts the following options:
 
